      "span_text": "Three groups are compared: healthy controls (HC, n and N = 8 in SUIT1), horses affected by polysaccharide storage myopathy (PSSM, n = 13 in SUIT1 and n = 14 in SUIT2, N = 5), and horses affected by rhabdomyolysis of unknown origin (RUO, n = 11 in SUIT1 and 2, N = 4). Two states (OXPHOS and ET-capacities) and three pathways (N for NADH pathway, S for succinate pathway and NS for NADH and succinate pathway) are included. Subscript 1 and 2 indicates the data coming from SUIT 1 and 2 respectively. Values are presented as the median (min-max) for each group. Values from HC were not available from our biobank for gm muscle in SUIT2. No significant differences were found between the three groups 0 Fig. 3 Respiratory parameters in the triceps brachii (tb) expressed as flux control ratios (FCR), over the maximal ET-capacity with substrates feeding electrons into the NADH and the succinate pathways simultaneously (NS). N and n are defined as for Fig.2 [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] ) and also show a greater contribution of NADH-linked pathway over both NADH and succinate pathways (NS pathway) and succinate pathway (S pathway) in type I-PSSM compared to HC."
